article.description: — Kamari Brown posted 12 points as Georgia Southern narrowly beat Troy 67-64 in overtime on Friday night.
article.headline: Brown leads Georgia Southern past Troy 67-64 in OT
article.linkText: Brown leads Georgia Southern past Troy 67-64 in OT
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- — Kamari Brown posted 12 points as Georgia Southern narrowly beat Troy 67-64 in overtime on Friday night. Zack Bryant had 12 points for Georgia Southern (8-6, 2/3 Sun Belt Conference). Kam Woods scored a season-high 23 points for the Trojans (6-6, 1-2). Khalyl Waters added 12 points and nine rebounds. Zay Williams had 11 points and nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
